main event: Three circular objects, comparable in size to the lights of a commercial airliner, were observed in Elkhorn, Wisconsin on May 25, 1957.
interesting points: The objects were observed for two minutes.
The objects had a red and white color, with a round shape.
The objects made a normal noise.
Two other observers saw only the white object and believed it to be a flare.
The report is a Project 10073 record card, which was a government program that investigated UFO sightings.
sighted object: three circular objects, red and white in color
